Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with geometric algorithms for computing minimum-width double-strip and parallelogram annulus. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents several algorithms for the problem. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the problem involves discrete structures such as points and regions in the plane. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is relevant as the problem deals with regions in the plane and their visualization. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely as the paper does not focus on the complexity analysis of the algorithms.
